  1159	        // L1 is an independent value check: our spectra_data m/z (f64) is compared bit-exact, per
  1160	        // spectrum, against the m/z array re-read directly from small.RAW (Scan.FromFile().SegmentedScan
  1161	        // .Positions) -- the source is NOT derived from our archive. The Thermo SegmentedScan returns
  1162	        // Positions sorted but Intensities in acquisition order (the two arrays are not index-paired and
  1163	        // their nonzero counts differ from the writer's realigned output), so re-deriving the exact
  1164	        // per-point intensity pairing from the SegmentedScan alone would require re-implementing the
  1165	        // reader's internal realignment. The differential suite (MzPeakDifferentialTests) compares
  1166	        // intensities value-for-value only over the reference-profile spectra. To avoid overclaiming
  1167	        // beyond that scope, this test asserts L2 here as a structural invariant for every emitted
  1168	        // spectrum (intensity is f32, finite, and the per-spectrum point count equals
  1169	        // number_of_data_points) and additionally runs an independent intensity check against an mzML
  1170	        // re-export of the same RAW for every spectrum that has a clean point-for-point correspondence,
  1171	        // so the value-equality claim rests on a source not derived from our archive.
