   365	   - What we know: the Rust `encode_arrow` returns `(0.0, 0.0, empty)` for an empty/all-null slice, and `decode_arrow` early-returns 0 points when `start==0 && end==0`.
   366	   - What's unclear: TRFP spectra are non-empty after the existing per-scan filtering, so empty windows shouldn't arise; `null_chunk_every_k` already omits empty windows.
