.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:12:2. **There is NO `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` column in delta mode.** The chunk struct has exactly **6 fields**. The Numpress byte column is added *only* when the encoding is NumpressLinear (Phase 3), not present-but-empty in delta mode. [VERIFIED: pyarrow dump + `ChunkingStrategy::extra_arrays` returns `vec![]` for Delta]
.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:23:- Emit the data facets in the reference **chunk layout** instead of point layout; make chunked the **new default** (`--point` restores v1 point layout). Lossless (delta-encoded m/z). Numpress (Phase 3) plugs into the `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` slot later. Chromatograms stay point layout (the reference keeps them point).
.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:28:- Streaming: reuse the Phase-1 streaming handle; chunk rows stream in row groups exactly like point rows. Needs `list<f64>`/`list<f32>` scalar-list columns with rep/def levels.
.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:39:- Numpress linear compression of `mz_chunk_values` (Phase 3). The `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` column belongs to Phase 3, NOT this phase.
.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:40:- Chromatogram chunking (reference keeps chromatograms point; CONTEXT keeps them point).
