.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:243:**Key insight:** The reference's "delta" layout is not a plain consecutive-delta list. It is a *null-marked, zero-pair-suppressed, absolute-restart-after-null* scheme. Reproducing it faithfully is the entire difficulty of this phase; the Parquet plumbing is already solved.
.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:259:**How to avoid:** Emit exactly 6 fields in delta mode. The Numpress column is a Phase-3 concern.
.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/RESEARCH.md:348:| `mz_numpress_linear_bytes` present-but-empty in delta | Column ABSENT in delta (6-field struct) | Do not add the column this phase |
