.planning/phases/02-chunked-layout/02-01-SUMMARY.md:106:The authoritative reference `refs/mzPeak/small.chunked.mzpeak` emits `chromatograms_data` in CHUNK layout (time_chunk_start/end/values, chunk_encoding=MS:1003089, intensity, ms_level). Phase 2 deliberately keeps `chromatograms_data` POINT: the validator has no chromatogram structural rule and the TIC is tiny, so chunking yields negligible benefit. **The earlier "the reference keeps chromatograms point" claim is false and was not propagated.** Full chromatogram chunking for structural parity is deferred to Phase 5.
